#page-nav.row
    %h1.red.title TUTORING
    %p.description.medium-7.columns
        Academic StratEDGEy provides high quality, results-oriented tutoring and skill-building workshops for middle and high school students.
    .sections.medium-4.medium-offset-1.columns
        %h2.red-strong.show-for-small-only
            Sections
        %ul
            %li
                %a{href: "#page-multi"}
                    Subject-Based Tutoring

.row
    .panel-title#page-multi
        %h2.red-strong
            Subject-Based Tutoring
    .bordered-panel
        %p
            Through convenient hourly sessions, we focus on academic improvement and confidence building. The goal: to provide students with the tools and structure they need to excel academically. While colleges care about leadership & character development, GPA and standardized test scores are of the utmost importance.  

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                Tutoring: Format & Pricing
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Group: 40 per student/hour
                            %li
                                Packet-Only: 40 per take-home study packet
                            %li
                                Semi-private (two people): 45 per student/hour
                            %li
                                Private (one-to-one): 70 per hour

.row
    .panel-title#page-multi
        %h2.red-strong
            Academic StratEDGEy: Subjects Offered
    .bordered-panel
        %p
            Bree Koziara, Ed.M. Harvard University and Founder of Academic StratEDGEy has over ten years of tutoring experience. Bree is passionate about the Humanities, especially history, will help you successfully navigate 8th grade US, AP World, and APUSH from Day 1 through her AP History Summer Boot Camps, weekly group tutoring sessions, and AP Exam review program.

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                US History/Geography (8th grade)
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Weekly US History group lessons (1 hr/wk) 
                            %li
                                Teach course fundamentals and lecture on chapter-based content. Provide take-home study packet.
                            %li
                                Quarterly benchmark and final rewivews. 

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                AP World History (10th grade)
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Weekly AP World History group lessons (1 hr/wk)
                            %li
                                Monthly essay workshops throughout the year: Compare & Contrast Essay, Document-Based Question Essay, Continuity & Change Over Time Essay.  
                            %li
                                AP World History Exam: Structured review program.

        .service-item
            %h3.title
                AP U.S. History (11th grade)
            .description.row
                .margined.large-12.columns
                    .bordered-panel
                        %ul
                            %li
                                Weekly APUSH group lessons (1 hr/wk)
                            %li
                                Monthly essay workshops throughout the year: Document-Based Question Essay, 2 Standard Essay Questions.
                            %li
                                APUSH Exam: Structured review program.                            
